**Human edit protection convention (my design — needs your sign-off)**

Proposed: any paragraph manually edited by a property manager carries a `<!-- bac:human -->` HTML comment. The AST merger treats these nodes as immutable — it will never overwrite, append to, or delete them. A `## 🔒 Manager Notes` section is additionally treated as immutable at the section level regardless of sentinel presence. Simple, auditable, requires zero UI.

